<section>
  <title>SystemStudio Files and Folders</title>

  <para><application class="software">SystemStudio</application> has several
  key files and folders, listed in the table below.</para>

  <para><informaltable>

      <tgroup cols="2">
        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry>/etc/systemstudio/systemstudio.conf</entry>

            <entry><application>SystemStudio</application> looks
            for this file to locate systemstudio configuration. See the
            systemstudio and systemstudio.conf man pages for more information.
            This file is optional and does not exist in the default SystemStudio
            installation.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>/usr/bin/systemstudio</entry>

            <entry>The <command>systemstudio</command> command.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry>/usr/lib/python<varname>$version</varname>/site-packages/systemstudio</entry>

            <entrytbl cols="1">
              <tbody>
                <row>
                  <entry>Python code for <application
                  class="software">SystemStudio</application>, where
                  <varname>$version</varname> is the <application
                  class="software">Python</application> version.</entry>
                </row>
              </tbody>
            </entrytbl>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry>/usr/share/doc/systemstudio-<varname>$version</varname></entry>

            <entry>Documentation for <application
            class="software">SystemStudio</application>, where
            <varname>$version</varname> is the <application
            class="software">SystemStudio</application> version.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry>/usr/share/systemstudio/schemas</entry>

            <entry>Relax NG schemas for system definition validation.
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>/var/cache/systemstudio/</entry>

            <entry>SystemStudio stores cached content in this folder. See
            the systemstudio and systemstudio.conf man pages for cache-related
            options.
            </entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry>/var/log/systemstudio.log</entry>

            <entry>SystemStudio's default log file.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry>/var/www/html/systems/</entry>

            <entry>SystemStudio publishes completed system repositories to  
            this folder by default. An alternative location can be specified on
            a per-system basis within a system definition.
            </entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable></para>

</section>
